				<h2>Math Equations</h2>
				<p>Math equations can be specified with LaTeX:</p>
				<MathEquation latex="x=\frac{-b\pm\sqrt{b^2-4ac}}{2a}" />
				<p>Using the label option you can label your equation:</p>
				<MathEquation latex="\Delta x=\int_{t_0}^{t_1} v(t)dt" label="(1.1)" />
				<p>You can also include math inline with other text, such as <latex>\alpha = \omega t</latex>.</p>
				<h2>HTML</h2>
				<p>In general HTML usage is not recommended since Obojobo cannot easily parse or understand HTML content and text selection is not accurate. However HTML allows you to do things which are not possible with standard Obojobo components.</p>
				<HTML html="<div style='background:#f1f1f1;padding:2em;'><h1>Custom HTML</h1><p>Plain HTML code is supported.</p></div>" />
				<h2>Buttons</h2>
